reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars CHECK YOUR BIOS VERSION before upgrading. You're welcome.
reviews.reviewText: Awesome CPU, great performance and bang for the buck. Low power draw, keeps cool even under load. Installation is fairly easy if you've installed CPUs before. Just watch a youtube how to do it. The only problem I had with it was I didn't see the little pamphlet in the box that said to upgrade my BIOS version before upgrading. Unfortunately, I was one version outdated. Had to uninstall, reinstall the old CPU, do a BIOS update which was a B, then do the swap again. Needless to say, went through a whole tube of thermal paste by the time I was done (speaking of, this does not include the paste nor the cooler).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Powerful Performer That Stands the Test of Time
reviews.reviewText: I've purchased this twice now, that's how much I love it.The AMD Ryzen™ 7 5700X desktop processor may belong to the last generation, but it still packs quite a punch and delivers an impressive performance that doesn't disappoint.Unleashing Power with 8 Cores and 16 Threads:With its 8-core, 16-thread configuration, the Ryzen™ 7 5700X is a true multitasking powerhouse. It effortlessly handles demanding tasks, making it ideal for gamers and content creators alike.Seamless Gaming Experience:When it comes to gaming, this processor is a force to be reckoned with. It delivers smooth and lag-free gameplay, and the 8 cores ensure that modern games run like a dream, even with demanding graphics.Editing Videos Like a Pro:For content creators and video editors, the Ryzen™ 7 5700X is a reliable companion. Its multithreaded performance shines during video editing tasks, reducing rendering times and enhancing overall productivity.Unlocked for Overclocking:Enthusiasts will appreciate the unlocked nature of this processor, allowing for easy overclocking to squeeze out even more performance when needed.Compatible with AM4 Socket:The Ryzen™ 7 5700X fits the AM4 socket, making it compatible with a wide range of motherboards. This ensures future upgradability and versatility in building your dream system.Reliable Cooling Solutions:The processor comes with a capable stock cooler that does a commendable job at keeping temperatures in check during regular use.Great Value for Performance:Though it's from the last generation, the Ryzen™ 7 5700X continues to offer excellent value for its performance. It competes admirably with newer counterparts in its price range.Future-Proof for Everyday Tasks:For everyday computing tasks, this processor is future-proof. It's more than capable of handling web browsing, office work, and other day-to-day activities with ease.Final Verdict:In conclusion, the AMD Ryzen™ 7 5700X 8-Core, 16-Thread Unlocked Desktop Processor is a testament to AMD's commitment to delivering powerful and efficient processors. While it may belong to the last generation, its performance is nothing short of impressive. Gamers, content creators, and everyday users will find a lot to love in this processor, thanks to its multitasking capabilities and smooth gaming experience. If you're looking for a cost-effective option that can handle both gaming and productivity tasks without breaking the bank, the Ryzen™ 7 5700X is undoubtedly worth considering. It's a reliable performer that stands the test of time and continues to shine in various computing scenarios.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great For The Price
reviews.reviewText: For this price range, this is the best CPU you can get. It is very fast, stays pretty cool, and is obviously an easy install.One thing I will say is since this is a new-ish CPU, you may need to update your bios for certain motherboards. I had to on a Tomohawk MAX.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for video editing
reviews.reviewText: I upgraded from the Ryzen 5 3600 which was terrible for video editing. With this new cpu, I’m able to do video editing and use adobe products flawlessly even while streaming videos on my other monitor at the same time. Definitely worth it. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid and Powerful CPU
reviews.reviewText: I love this CPU. I'm upgrading from a Ryzen 3600x and I noticed the speed upon turning on my pc, with it booting up so fast and running smooth. I also got a RX 6800 and it's compatible with it with no bottleneck. I got the cpu for $182 black Friday. If you can grab with that price than it's worth it. Just as good as the Ryzen 5 5800x, but uses less battery consumption which is great for me since I use a lot of RGB for my computer. Note! It doesn't come with a air cooler. Need to buy your own and it can't be a basic cooler. You need a mid tier fan or low tier AIO to keep it cool. Noise is silent depending on what fan you get. Good for any AMD B450 motherboard.

reviews.reviewText: Si vas a hacer un upgrade o a armar un nuevo rig con AM4, esta es la mejor opción del momento por precio y rendimiento, además de que con un tdp de 65 W se mantiene a buena temperatura (~60°C), aún después de largas jornadas de uso intenso, con un enfriador de aire económico.

reviews.reviewTitle: Solid CPU for your money even this long after release
reviews.reviewText: At this point in time with AM5 out now, this CPU still remains a very solid "bang for your buck" CPU if building a previous-gen system. I was upgrading on a budget and didn't have the need for bleeding edge performance - this CPU with a new mainboard and RAM hit the perfect sweet spot for low cost and high performance and was a very notable upgrade over my older 2700X CPU and will last me for easily another 5++ years to come! Get them while you can - I assume AM4 will continue winding down at this point.

Jemand anderes brauchte günstig schnell einen Prozessor, also musste ich den alten freimachen. Nach einem Firmware-Update vor CPU-Wechsel lief die AMD-CPU ohne Probleme im ASUS TUF B450. Fühlbar mehr Leistung schon im Desktopbetrieb und das bei reduziertem Verbrauch. Eigentlich muss man dem Hardwareteilekäufer sowas nicht rezensieren, und ich kaufe Hardware ungern bei Amazon, aber die CPU war hier zu der Zeit am günstigsten, erfüllte die Erwartungen und ermöglichte tatsächlich ein Upgrade, bevor man auf die im Moment noch sauteure AM5-Plattform umsteigen muss. Amazons Lieferpraxis war ausschlaggebend.Und einen CPU-Wechsel ohne Boardwechsel hatte ich seit Jahren nicht, wechsele allerdings auch nur alle paar Jahre die Plattform aus und bleibe auf mittleren CPUs in meinem Szenario. Bei Full-HD Gaming ist in meinem Fall die GraKa der Flaschenhals. 64GB Ram hab ich mir auch gegönnt. Alles schön entspannt und ein bißchen Ruhe, bis die AM5-Preise sich einkriegen.Technische Daten und Benchmarks gibts im Netz und die Packung brauche ich nicht bewerten, ich würde auch Trays verbauen.

Ce processeur est incroyable, rien à redire. Si, comme moi, vous avez par exemple un Ryzen 2700 et que vous souhaitez mettre à niveau votre PC, foncez ! N'oubliez pas de mettre à jour votre BIOS si vous possédez une carte mère B450 ou X470.C'est super de voir une telle amélioration dans les performances de jeu ! Passer d'un Ryzen 2700 et d'une RX 6750 XT à quelque chose qui vous permet de jouer à des jeux comme "7 Days to Die" à des vitesses dépassant les 100 FPS est une grande avancée.
